  ---
  Pagination Guide

  Both endpoints support two pagination modes — pick one per request, don't mix them.

  Offset-based (simple)
  GET /integrations/catalog?take=10&skip=0   # page 1
  GET /integrations/catalog?take=10&skip=10  # page 2
  GET /integrations/catalog?take=10&skip=20  # page 3

  Cursor-based (stable, recommended for large datasets)

  Use nextCursor from each response as the cursor param for the next page. Stop when nextCursor is null.

  GET /alternatives/catalog?take=10
  → nextCursor: "clx2xyz..."

  GET /alternatives/catalog?take=10&cursor=clx2xyz...
  → nextCursor: "clxaabc..."

  GET /alternatives/catalog?take=10&cursor=clxaabc...
  → nextCursor: null   ← end of results

